project_id.description: Required. ID of the Cloud project where the trace data is stored.

view.description: Optional. Type of data returned for traces in the list. Default is ``MINIMAL``.

page_size.description: Optional. Maximum number of traces to return. If not specified or <= 0, the implementation selects a reasonable value.  The implementation may return fewer traces than the requested page size.

page_token.description: Token identifying the page of results to return. If provided, use the value of the ``next_page_token`` field from a previous request.

start_time.description: Start of the time interval (inclusive) during which the trace data was collected from the application.

end_time.description: End of the time interval (inclusive) during which the trace data was collected from the application.

filter.description: Optional. A filter against labels for the request.  By default, searches use prefix matching. To specify exact match, prepend a plus symbol (``+``) to the search term. Multiple terms are ANDed. Syntax:  -  ``root:NAME_PREFIX`` or ``NAME_PREFIX``: Return traces where any root span starts with ``NAME_PREFIX``. -  ``+root:NAME`` or ``+NAME``: Return traces where any root span's name is exactly ``NAME``. -  ``span:NAME_PREFIX``: Return traces where any span starts with ``NAME_PREFIX``. -  ``+span:NAME``: Return traces where any span's name is exactly ``NAME``. -  ``latency:DURATION``: Return traces whose overall latency is greater or equal to than ``DURATION``. Accepted units are nanoseconds (``ns``), milliseconds (``ms``), and seconds (``s``). Default is ``ms``. For example, ``latency:24ms`` returns traces whose overall latency is greater than or equal to 24 milliseconds. -  ``label:LABEL_KEY``: Return all traces containing the specified label key (exact match, case-sensitive) regardless of the key:value pair's value (including empty values). -  ``LABEL_KEY:VALUE_PREFIX``: Return all traces containing the specified label key (exact match, case-sensitive) whose value starts with ``VALUE_PREFIX``. Both a key and a value must be specified. -  ``+LABEL_KEY:VALUE``: Return all traces containing a key:value pair exactly matching the specified text. Both a key and a value must be specified. -  ``method:VALUE``: Equivalent to ``/http/method:VALUE``. -  ``url:VALUE``: Equivalent to ``/http/url:VALUE``.

order_by.description: Optional. Field used to sort the returned traces. Can be one of the following:  -  ``trace_id`` -  ``name`` (``name`` field of root span in the trace) -  ``duration`` (difference between ``end_time`` and ``start_time`` fields of the root span) -  ``start`` (``start_time`` field of the root span)  Descending order can be specified by appending ``desc`` to the sort field (for example, ``name desc``).  Only one sort field is permitted.

cause.description: Cause that the packet is dropped.

resource_uri.description: URI of the resource that caused the drop.

source_ip.description: Source IP address of the dropped packet (if relevant).

destination_ip.description: Destination IP address of the dropped packet (if relevant).

region.description: Region of the dropped packet (if relevant).

load_balancer.description: Display information of the load balancers. Deprecated in favor of the ``load_balancer_backend_info`` field, not used in new tests.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``step_info``.

health_check_uri.description: URI of the health check for the load balancer. Deprecated and no longer populated as different load balancer backends might have different health checks.

display_name.description: Name of a Compute Engine instance or network endpoint.

uri.description: URI of a Compute Engine instance or network endpoint.

health_check_firewall_state.description: State of the health check firewall configuration.

health_check_allowing_firewall_rules.description: A list of firewall rule URIs allowing probes from health check IP ranges.

health_check_blocking_firewall_rules.description: A list of firewall rule URIs blocking probes from health check IP ranges.

backend_type.description: Type of load balancer's backend configuration.

network.description: Display information of a Google Cloud network.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``step_info``.

display_name.description: Name of a Compute Engine network.

uri.description: URI of a Compute Engine network.

matched_subnet_uri.description: URI of the subnet matching the source IP address of the test.

matched_ip_range.description: The IP range of the subnet matching the source IP address of the test.

region.description: The region of the subnet matching the source IP address of the test.

gke_master.description: Display information of a Google Kubernetes Engine cluster master.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``step_info``.

cluster_network_uri.description: URI of a GKE cluster network.

internal_ip.description: Internal IP address of a GKE cluster control plane.

external_ip.description: External IP address of a GKE cluster control plane.

dns_endpoint.description: DNS endpoint of a GKE cluster control plane.

cloud_sql_instance.description: Display information of a Cloud SQL instance.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``step_info``.

display_name.description: Name of a Cloud SQL instance.

uri.description: URI of a Cloud SQL instance.

network_uri.description: URI of a Cloud SQL instance network or empty string if the instance does not have one.

internal_ip.description: Internal IP address of a Cloud SQL instance.

external_ip.description: External IP address of a Cloud SQL instance.

region.description: Region in which the Cloud SQL instance is running.

redis_instance.description: Display information of a Redis Instance.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``step_info``.

display_name.description: Name of a Cloud Redis Instance.

uri.description: URI of a Cloud Redis Instance.

network_uri.description: URI of a Cloud Redis Instance network.

primary_endpoint_ip.description: Primary endpoint IP address of a Cloud Redis Instance.

read_endpoint_ip.description: Read endpoint IP address of a Cloud Redis Instance (if applicable).

region.description: Region in which the Cloud Redis Instance is defined.

redis_cluster.description: Display information of a Redis Cluster.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``step_info``.

uri.description: URI of a Redis Cluster in format "projects/{project_id}/locations/{location}/clusters/{cluster_id}".

network_uri.description: URI of a Redis Cluster network in format "projects/{project_id}/global/networks/{network_id}".

discovery_endpoint_ip_address.description: Discovery endpoint IP address of a Redis Cluster.

secondary_endpoint_ip_address.description: Secondary endpoint IP address of a Redis Cluster.

location.description: Name of the region in which the Redis Cluster is defined. For example, "us-central1".

cloud_function.description: Display information of a Cloud Function.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``step_info``.

location.description: Location in which the Cloud Function is deployed.

version_id.description: Latest successfully deployed version id of the Cloud Function.

app_engine_version.description: Display information of an App Engine service version.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``step_info``.

display_name.description: Name of an App Engine version.

uri.description: URI of an App Engine version.

runtime.description: Runtime of the App Engine version.

environment.description: App Engine execution environment for a version.

cloud_run_revision.description: Display information of a Cloud Run revision.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``step_info``.

display_name.description: Name of a Cloud Run revision.

uri.description: URI of a Cloud Run revision.

location.description: Location in which this revision is deployed.

service_uri.description: URI of Cloud Run service this revision belongs to.

nat.description: Display information of a NAT.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``step_info``.

protocol.description: IP protocol in string format, for example: "TCP", "UDP", "ICMP".

network_uri.description: URI of the network where NAT translation takes place.

old_source_ip.description: Source IP address before NAT translation.

new_source_ip.description: Source IP address after NAT translation.

old_destination_ip.description: Destination IP address before NAT translation.

new_destination_ip.description: Destination IP address after NAT translation.

old_source_port.description: Source port before NAT translation. Only valid when protocol is TCP or UDP.

new_source_port.description: Source port after NAT translation. Only valid when protocol is TCP or UDP.

old_destination_port.description: Destination port before NAT translation. Only valid when protocol is TCP or UDP.

new_destination_port.description: Destination port after NAT translation. Only valid when protocol is TCP or UDP.

router_uri.description: Uri of the Cloud Router. Only valid when type is CLOUD_NAT.

nat_gateway_name.description: The name of Cloud NAT Gateway. Only valid when type is CLOUD_NAT.

proxy_connection.description: Display information of a ProxyConnection.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``step_info``.

protocol.description: IP protocol in string format, for example: "TCP", "UDP", "ICMP".

old_source_ip.description: Source IP address of an original connection.

new_source_ip.description: Source IP address of a new connection.

old_destination_ip.description: Destination IP address of an original connection

new_destination_ip.description: Destination IP address of a new connection.

old_source_port.description: Source port of an original connection. Only valid when protocol is TCP or UDP.

new_source_port.description: Source port of a new connection. Only valid when protocol is TCP or UDP.

old_destination_port.description: Destination port of an original connection. Only valid when protocol is TCP or UDP.

new_destination_port.description: Destination port of a new connection. Only valid when protocol is TCP or UDP.

network_uri.description: URI of the network where connection is proxied.

load_balancer_backend_info.description: Display information of a specific load balancer backend.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``step_info``.

name.description: Display name of the backend. For example, it might be an instance name for the instance group backends, or an IP address and port for zonal network endpoint group backends.

instance_uri.description: URI of the backend instance (if applicable). Populated for instance group backends, and zonal NEG backends.

backend_service_uri.description: URI of the backend service this backend belongs to (if applicable).

instance_group_uri.description: URI of the instance group this backend belongs to (if applicable).

network_endpoint_group_uri.description: URI of the network endpoint group this backend belongs to (if applicable).

backend_bucket_uri.description: URI of the backend bucket this backend targets (if applicable).

psc_service_attachment_uri.description: URI of the PSC service attachment this PSC NEG backend targets (if applicable).

psc_google_api_target.description: PSC Google API target this PSC NEG backend targets (if applicable).

health_check_uri.description: URI of the health check attached to this backend (if applicable).

health_check_firewalls_config_state.description: Output only. Health check firewalls configuration state for the backend. This is a result of the static firewall analysis (verifying that health check traffic from required IP ranges to the backend is allowed or not). The backend might still be unhealthy even if these firewalls are configured. Please refer to the documentation for more information:  https://cloud.google.com/load-balancing/docs/firewall-rules

storage_bucket.description: Display information of a Storage Bucket. Used only for return traces.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``step_info``.

serverless_neg.description: Display information of a Serverless network endpoint group backend. Used only for return traces.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``step_info``.

neg_uri.description: URI of the serverless network endpoint group.

forward_trace_id.description: ID of trace. For forward traces, this ID is unique for each trace. For return traces, it matches ID of associated forward trace. A single forward trace can be associated with none, one or more than one return trace.
